javadoc: HttpsHostnameVerifier is required by HttpsURLConnection even if it does nothing. The verify method will only be invoked if the default behavior fails the connection attempt due to a hostname mismatch. @see HttpsURLConnection#setHostnameVerifier(HostnameVerifier)
name: HttpsHostnameVerifier
comment:
HttpsHostnameVerifier is required by HttpsURLConnection even
 if it does nothing.  The verify method will only be invoked if the default 
 behavior fails the connection attempt due to a hostname mismatch.
